.TH "batadv_hardif_no_broadcast" 9 "batadv_hardif_no_broadcast" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_hardif_no_broadcast \- check whether (re)broadcast is necessary
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" batadv_hardif_no_broadcast
.BI "(struct batadv_hard_iface *if_outgoing "  ","
.BI "u8 *orig_addr "  ","
.BI "u8 *orig_neigh "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "if_outgoing" 12
the outgoing interface checked and considered for (re)broadcast
.IP "orig_addr" 12
the originator of this packet
.IP "orig_neigh" 12
originator address of the forwarder we just got the packet from
(NULL if we originated)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Checks whether a packet needs to be (re)broadcasted on the given interface.
.SH "RETURN"
BATADV_HARDIF_BCAST_NORECIPIENT: No neighbor on interface
BATADV_HARDIF_BCAST_DUPFWD: Just one neighbor, but it is the forwarder
BATADV_HARDIF_BCAST_DUPORIG: Just one neighbor, but it is the originator
BATADV_HARDIF_BCAST_OK: Several neighbors, must broadcast
